Git is a version control system, to begin:
0. git config --global user.name "H.Hui"
   git config --global user.email "geo.hjhui@gmail.com"
1. mkdir dir to choose your work directory
2. cd dir 
3. git init to generate .git directory which includes configure files
4. write a text file (e.g. readme)
5. git add readme
6. git commit -m "wrote a readme file"
----------------------------------------------------------------
some useful commands:
git diff filename: check the change in your file
git status: check the status of your working directory)
